    "updated_at": "2016-12-17T04:23:38Z",
    "body": "As far as I am aware this is entirely expected behavior, if you want to launch a different process to perform background tasks on you should look into something like [`electron-workers`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/electron-workers) or implement something similar yourself.\r\n\r\nThe trick is forking your process with `ELECTRON_RUN_AS_NODE=true` 👍 \r\n\r\nIf you open a window and then hide it, it is still technically a window and I don't think we should be hiding it from that window menu (if it is even possible to do so)"
  },
